WEBVTT

00:00.709 --> 00:03.128
Previously
on "Promised Land"...

00:03.128 --> 00:04.922
You're in America now.
You should go by Joe.

00:04.922 --> 00:06.381
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:06.381 --> 00:07.841
Young Margaret: I know
you're in love with Joe.

00:07.841 --> 00:09.259
I'm in love with Billy.

00:09.259 --> 00:10.802
You love both of them.

00:10.802 --> 00:13.305
Get to work!
This is a war now.

00:13.305 --> 00:15.599
We like our chances.

00:15.599 --> 00:16.767
Joe:
Why didn't you tell me?

00:16.767 --> 00:18.727
I will regret that
for the rest of my life.

00:18.727 --> 00:19.811
I think
you should leave.

00:21.313 --> 00:22.648
I gave them my word!

00:22.648 --> 00:24.650
I'm reopening
negotiations.

00:24.650 --> 00:27.236
Joe Sandoval is
no longer capable

00:27.236 --> 00:28.195
of running Heritage House.

00:28.195 --> 00:29.696
Let's talk.

00:30.739 --> 00:33.700
♪♪

00:33.700 --> 00:35.285
You would be CEO.

00:35.285 --> 00:36.453
I'm CEO now.

00:36.453 --> 00:39.623
[ Sighs ] Veronica.

00:39.623 --> 00:41.250
If you were
fully empowered,

00:41.250 --> 00:43.085
would you have agreed
to come here tonight?

00:43.085 --> 00:46.129
You're just amassing shares,
and you want my 5%.

00:46.129 --> 00:49.424
Yes, I've acquired a large stake
in Heritage House,

00:49.424 --> 00:52.844
and, yes, I plan to propose
an alternate slate of directors

00:52.844 --> 00:54.137
at next week's
shareholders meeting.

00:54.137 --> 00:58.392
So, yes,
if I had your 5%,

00:58.392 --> 01:02.229
I'd be that much closer to being
able to ram that slate through.

01:02.229 --> 01:06.108
And in exchange for my shares,
I'd get...what, exactly?

01:06.108 --> 01:09.069
Stock options
for 20% of the company,

01:09.069 --> 01:11.613
with time-based vesting
starting on day one.

01:11.613 --> 01:13.865
At the end of each year,
additional shares

01:13.865 --> 01:16.285
at a pre-negotiated
strike price.

01:16.285 --> 01:18.912
At the end
of five years,

01:18.912 --> 01:23.166
you would be guaranteed
a 50% ownership stake.

01:24.334 --> 01:26.795
Let me repeat that.

01:26.795 --> 01:31.842
50% of the company
would be yours

01:31.842 --> 01:35.470
if you help me take over
Heritage House.

01:35.470 --> 01:39.308
♪♪

01:39.308 --> 01:41.727
[ Insects chirping ]

01:51.111 --> 01:53.030
Excuse me, sir?

01:53.030 --> 01:54.781
Hi. Um, sorry.

01:54.781 --> 01:56.491
My -- My truck,
it won't start.

01:56.491 --> 01:58.201
I'm already late, kid.

01:58.201 --> 02:00.287
I know, but my sister --
she's having a baby,

02:00.287 --> 02:01.997
and I'm --
I'm missing it.

02:01.997 --> 02:04.124
Her -- Her husband is a --
is a truck driver,

02:04.124 --> 02:05.292
so he's on the road
like you.

02:05.292 --> 02:07.377
I -- Please.

02:07.377 --> 02:08.920
Fine.
I'll -- I'll take a look.

02:08.920 --> 02:10.172
Thank you.

02:10.172 --> 02:11.715
Thank you, thank you.

02:13.508 --> 02:14.968
Alright, let's see.

02:16.261 --> 02:24.186
♪♪

02:25.562 --> 02:27.147
[ Exhales sharply ]

02:29.983 --> 02:32.778
♪♪

02:36.448 --> 02:38.575
Everything seems okay
to me.

02:38.575 --> 02:40.494
[ Engine sputters, starts ]

02:40.494 --> 02:41.787
Huh?

02:41.787 --> 02:43.246
Hey!

02:44.498 --> 02:46.625
Hey! Stop!

02:47.542 --> 02:49.086
My truck!

02:49.086 --> 02:51.213
Eso!

02:51.213 --> 02:53.632
[ Laughs ]

02:53.632 --> 02:55.217
[ Engine starts ]
Hey!

02:55.217 --> 02:58.178
Gracias, señor!

02:58.178 --> 03:01.181
♪♪

03:05.394 --> 03:09.439
♪♪

03:09.439 --> 03:12.776
♪ I left my soul ♪

03:14.319 --> 03:17.698
♪ On Californian soil ♪

03:33.755 --> 03:38.051
♪ And I never had a plan ♪

03:39.719 --> 03:43.682
♪ But I'm glad
I found you here ♪

03:43.682 --> 03:47.769
♪♪

03:57.154 --> 03:59.197
[ Sighs ]

03:59.614 --> 04:01.283
I've been trying to tell her
we're done all day,

04:01.283 --> 04:02.993
but she won't listen.

04:02.993 --> 04:04.578
Lettie: Still got
another hour in me.

04:04.578 --> 04:07.456
No, no. The mid-day sun is gonna
ferment the grapes too fast.

04:07.456 --> 04:09.166
And I can't afford
to pay you overtime.

04:09.166 --> 04:10.917
Fine,
but I'll be back tonight.

04:10.917 --> 04:12.210
No, you're done
for the day, Ma.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.920
I enjoy this, Mateo.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.589
It's harvest,
and everybody pitches in.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.340
Well, almost everybody.

04:17.340 --> 04:20.051
Hey, 30 years ago, I swore
I'd never touch another grape.

04:20.051 --> 04:21.761
[ Chuckles ]
Don't make a liar
out of me.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.597
[ Laughs ]

04:27.517 --> 04:29.227
So, have you made
a list?

04:29.227 --> 04:31.438
About what?

04:31.438 --> 04:33.064
The pros and cons
of leaving Joe.

04:33.064 --> 04:34.816
Oh, Rosa, come on.

04:34.816 --> 04:38.320
It helps me
with my patients,

04:38.320 --> 04:39.738
deciding which treatment
to go with.

04:39.738 --> 04:41.782
Yeah,
so now I'm a patient.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.742
If you were, I'd refer you
to another doctor.

04:43.742 --> 04:45.577
Oh, really, Dr. Rosa?

04:45.577 --> 04:47.370
Why?
'Cause I'm family.

04:47.370 --> 04:49.289
No. Because you're
way too difficult.

04:49.289 --> 04:51.792
[ Chuckles ]

04:51.792 --> 04:56.046
No, I understand
why Joe would be angry.

04:56.046 --> 04:58.173
I should have told him
what happened with his dad.

04:58.173 --> 04:59.674
Maybe.

04:59.674 --> 05:02.928
Then again, why stay with a man
you can't tell the truth to?

05:02.928 --> 05:05.180
So you think I'd be
better off with Billy?

05:05.180 --> 05:06.890
[ Chuckles ]

05:06.890 --> 05:08.892
You mean Billy,
who's now a priest?

05:08.892 --> 05:10.310
[ Chuckles ]

05:10.310 --> 05:12.062
[ Sighs ]

05:12.062 --> 05:13.814
Leave it to
that charming bastard

05:13.814 --> 05:15.690
to do the last thing
you'd expect.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.904
Did you violate
any vows?

05:20.904 --> 05:22.531
His or yours?
Rosa!

05:22.531 --> 05:25.992
Come on. No.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.577
Came close, but no.

05:27.577 --> 05:28.870
[ Clicks tongue ]
Ah.

05:28.870 --> 05:32.666
I think I know
where he went.

05:32.666 --> 05:33.959
Then why haven't you
gone to him?

05:33.959 --> 05:39.089
Because every time I'm about to,
I ask myself,

05:39.089 --> 05:42.175
"Am I truly in love
with him

05:42.175 --> 05:45.428
or with who I was
when I was with him?"

05:45.428 --> 05:47.222
At the end of the day,

05:47.222 --> 05:51.017
as long as you're happy,
does it matter?

05:51.017 --> 05:54.354
♪♪

06:00.861 --> 06:02.487
Gracias.

06:02.487 --> 06:04.322
[ Speaks Spanish ]

06:07.576 --> 06:09.870
It's your favorite
two weeks of the year.

06:09.870 --> 06:11.788
Yeah, we're running
a day shift today.

06:11.788 --> 06:13.456
That's how full
this harvest is.

06:13.456 --> 06:15.625
So where should we go?
What do you mean?

06:15.625 --> 06:18.461
Well, when the harvest is over,
I'm taking you somewhere.

06:18.461 --> 06:21.506
I'm thinking
Mexican wine country.

06:21.506 --> 06:22.841
Valle de Guadalupe.

06:22.841 --> 06:24.050
Nowhere near a grape,
please.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.927
[ Chuckles ]

06:25.927 --> 06:28.096
Okay. Then where?

06:28.096 --> 06:29.306
Disneyland.

06:29.306 --> 06:30.974
Oh, I forgot about
your Goofy thing.

06:30.974 --> 06:32.809
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.809 --> 06:34.936
Hey. Maybe the workers
will strike

06:34.936 --> 06:36.104
and we can fly down
tonight.

06:36.104 --> 06:37.814
No. Don't --
Don't even joke.

06:38.940 --> 06:41.568
I already pay 50%
of health coverage.

06:41.568 --> 06:44.487
Veronica agreed to 70%.
We shook on it.

06:44.487 --> 06:46.781
No, you and Veronica
shook on it.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.450
So everything we agreed to
is out the window?

06:48.450 --> 06:49.451
Not everything.

06:49.451 --> 06:51.369
I'm okay with
a 3% wage increase.

06:51.369 --> 06:53.913
We asked for 6%.
And I'm giving you 3%.

06:53.913 --> 06:55.123
Better than nothing.

06:55.123 --> 06:57.584
Well, this is obviously
getting us nowhere.

06:57.584 --> 06:58.835
We've been talking
for hours,

06:58.835 --> 07:01.963
and you haven't yielded
one single deal point.

07:01.963 --> 07:05.342
One of us is willing to
negotiate in good faith.

07:05.342 --> 07:06.718
The other one isn't.

07:06.718 --> 07:08.553
You know
where to reach me.

07:09.804 --> 07:11.473
[ Door closes ]

07:11.473 --> 07:13.933
Do you really wanna piss him off
in the middle of a harvest?

07:13.933 --> 07:15.310
I'm not worried.

07:15.310 --> 07:16.853
You will be
if the workers walk out.

07:16.853 --> 07:20.231
Trust me.
No one is walking out.

07:20.231 --> 07:21.650
♪♪

07:21.650 --> 07:25.403
[ Workers chanting in Spanish ]

07:30.825 --> 07:33.036
[ Crowd booing ]

07:45.840 --> 07:46.883
I'm sorry, Margaret.

07:46.883 --> 07:48.301
I've heard worse.

07:49.886 --> 07:51.179
I'm curious.

07:51.179 --> 07:53.056
What do you think
you accomplished?

07:53.056 --> 07:56.518
Pues, ahora it's harder
for the scabs

07:56.518 --> 07:58.228
to get on the vineyard.

07:58.228 --> 08:00.855
If people want to work, a
truck's not going to stop them.

08:00.855 --> 08:03.108
Just has to stop them long
enough to read one of these.

08:03.108 --> 08:05.360
Mira.

08:05.360 --> 08:08.113
When they see why we fight,
they won't go through that gate.

08:09.406 --> 08:11.408
My father is very upset.

08:13.993 --> 08:15.704
Tell him to come down.

08:15.704 --> 08:16.746
We can talk about it.

08:16.746 --> 08:18.456
He's done talking, Joe.

08:18.456 --> 08:23.670
♪♪

08:30.301 --> 08:33.138
[ Engine starts ]

08:33.138 --> 08:38.852
♪♪

08:38.852 --> 08:41.354
Tomás:
Yeah, tonight at 7:00.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.273
No, everyone needs
to be there.

08:43.273 --> 08:45.400
And let them know I'm
recommending a "yes" vote.

08:45.400 --> 08:46.985
[ Cellphone beeps ]
You're calling a strike?

08:46.985 --> 08:49.070
Your father
left us no choice.

08:49.070 --> 08:50.947
[ Exhales sharply ]
He'd never risk it.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.157
Not in the middle
of harvest.

08:52.157 --> 08:53.033
Are you sure
about that?

08:55.285 --> 08:58.413
No. No.

08:58.413 --> 08:59.539
Truth is,
when it comes to my father,

08:59.539 --> 09:01.416
I'm not sure
about anything anymore.

09:01.416 --> 09:03.918
Look,
just delay the vote.

09:03.918 --> 09:06.880
There may be a change
in leadership happening.

09:06.880 --> 09:10.091
Margaret's making a play
for Heritage House.

09:10.091 --> 09:12.552
She's offering me the moon
to stay on as CEO.

09:12.552 --> 09:13.887
So what are you
thinking?

09:13.887 --> 09:16.681
Well, she's saying
all the right things.

09:16.681 --> 09:18.266
But then again,
so did my father.

09:18.266 --> 09:19.476
Get it in writing.

09:19.476 --> 09:21.519
Contracts are like origami
to them.

09:21.519 --> 09:24.064
You bend them
any way you want.

09:24.064 --> 09:26.107
They're cut
from the same cloth.

09:26.107 --> 09:27.859
As long as one of them
owns the company,

09:27.859 --> 09:29.235
I'll never be able to run it
the way I want.

09:31.071 --> 09:34.157
I need someone else
to buy Heritage House.

09:34.157 --> 09:35.617
Got someone in mind?

09:35.617 --> 09:37.410
Yeah.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.412
Me.

09:39.412 --> 09:40.538
Just can't do it alone.

09:40.538 --> 09:43.792
[ Cellphone buzzes, beeps ]

09:43.792 --> 09:45.877
This is Tomás.

09:45.877 --> 09:47.212
I'll be right there.

09:48.838 --> 09:50.548
Looks like your father
beat us to the punch.

09:50.548 --> 09:52.217
♪♪

09:52.217 --> 09:54.427
[ Indistinct shouting ]

09:54.427 --> 09:56.471
Javi.

09:56.471 --> 09:57.639
Javi, what's going on?

09:57.639 --> 09:59.099
Joe ordered me
to lock the workers out.

10:01.017 --> 10:01.935
So who are these guys?

10:03.186 --> 10:04.479
Replacements.

10:05.855 --> 10:08.233
This way. Come on.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.443
♪♪

10:10.443 --> 10:12.237
My father hired scabs?

10:12.237 --> 10:14.197
Somebody's gotta
pick the grapes.

10:14.197 --> 10:15.740
Excuse me.

10:15.740 --> 10:19.077
♪♪

10:25.083 --> 10:26.793
So, how many of the half-tons
did we fill?

10:26.793 --> 10:28.419
12.

10:28.419 --> 10:29.712
We only filled 12
of the half-tons?

10:29.712 --> 10:31.881
What? You wanted us
to do everything by hand.

10:31.881 --> 10:33.258
I can rent us
a harvester.

10:33.258 --> 10:34.801
It's not too late.

10:36.344 --> 10:37.554
By hand it is.

10:37.554 --> 10:38.930
[ Horn honks ]

10:40.807 --> 10:42.392
Oh, God. Who drives a Porsche
to a vineyard?

10:42.392 --> 10:45.186
Mateo.

10:45.186 --> 10:46.604
[ Speaks Spanish ]

10:46.604 --> 10:48.731
I got your text.
Yeah?

10:48.731 --> 10:50.233
I thought your guys
could pick our rows.

10:50.233 --> 10:51.359
You mean your rows.

10:51.359 --> 10:52.569
I'm out of the sangria business,
remember?

10:52.569 --> 10:54.487
[ Sighs ] Fine. My rows.
So what's the problem?

10:54.487 --> 10:55.947
I think I got
a bunch of no-shows.

10:55.947 --> 10:58.074
I got a small crew.
I need them all on my tract.

10:58.074 --> 11:00.243
Hell, I got Lettie
picking grapes.

11:00.243 --> 11:01.703
Oh, my God.
Is there a video?

11:01.703 --> 11:03.955
Carmen, if your grapes don't
get picked the next day or so,

11:03.955 --> 11:04.831
your sugar levels
will be too high.

11:04.831 --> 11:06.624
Your whole crop
will be ruined.

11:06.624 --> 11:08.918
So I've had the business all of
a week, and I could go under?

11:08.918 --> 11:10.003
That's what you're saying?

11:10.003 --> 11:11.087
It's not your first harvest,
Carmen.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.338
You've got to anticipate
these things.

11:12.338 --> 11:14.299
And a life lesson
in the bargain.

11:14.299 --> 11:15.466
Thanks, 'Teo.

11:15.466 --> 11:17.343
What, are you scared
of getting your hands dirty?

11:23.183 --> 11:25.310
Hey.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.896
You brought the business this
far by thinking outside the box.

11:27.896 --> 11:29.147
You're gonna stop
doing that now?

11:32.901 --> 11:34.402
Reporter: Even a late rally
on Wall Street

11:34.402 --> 11:35.570
isn't helping the stock price

11:35.570 --> 11:37.572
of Sonoma Valley's
Heritage House.

11:37.572 --> 11:40.533
The esteemed winemaker's shares
continue to take a hit on --

11:41.284 --> 11:43.369
What the hell is he doing?
I don't know.

11:43.369 --> 11:44.746
Stock's down 4%.

11:46.748 --> 11:47.916
Can I trust you
with something?

11:47.916 --> 11:49.709
Yeah.

11:49.709 --> 11:52.128
Margaret offered me
a deal.

11:52.128 --> 11:54.756
If I help her
take over Heritage House,

11:54.756 --> 11:56.633
she gives me
expanded CEO powers

11:56.633 --> 11:59.719
and a 50% stake in the company
within five years.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.387
V, that's amazing.

12:01.387 --> 12:03.181
Are you gonna take it?

12:03.181 --> 12:06.559
Apá's win-at-all-costs mentality
is gonna destroy this company.

12:06.559 --> 12:08.061
But?

12:08.061 --> 12:09.729
But our mother's
no better.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.981
[ Chuckles ] Yeah, I can't
disagree with you there.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.775
So what if we took over
Heritage House?

12:16.611 --> 12:20.782
Think about it.
You and I each own 5%.

12:20.782 --> 12:23.451
Carmen, Mateo, and Junior --
that's 25%.

12:23.451 --> 12:26.412
No, that's 15%.

12:26.412 --> 12:28.414
Mateo doesn't have
any shares,

12:28.414 --> 12:29.332
and Junior's are held
in a trust.

12:29.332 --> 12:30.833
We can't count on those.

12:30.833 --> 12:33.211
Lettie owns 5%.
Oh, please.

12:33.211 --> 12:35.588
You think Lettie's gonna
turn her back on Joe?

12:35.588 --> 12:37.131
Did you ever think
I would?

12:37.131 --> 12:39.968
Let's just say
we control 20%.

12:39.968 --> 12:43.721
With the chaos at the top of the
company and the stock tanking,

12:43.721 --> 12:46.724
shareholders meet
next week,

12:46.724 --> 12:48.935
I bet we can get enough of them
to come our way.

12:48.935 --> 12:50.520
Yeah, maybe.

12:50.520 --> 12:52.522
But we'll be fighting
a two-front war.

12:52.522 --> 12:54.482
Joe and Margaret are no joke
in a street fight.

12:54.482 --> 12:56.067
Oh, and we are?

12:56.067 --> 12:58.069
[ Chuckles ]

12:58.069 --> 12:59.737
And I thought family dinners
were awkward before.

12:59.737 --> 13:02.323
Antonio,
we can do this.

13:05.576 --> 13:07.328
I need a few hours
to think about it.

13:07.328 --> 13:09.080
I'll talk to the others
and let you know what they say.

13:09.080 --> 13:14.544
♪♪

13:14.544 --> 13:20.883
♪♪

13:20.883 --> 13:22.385
Reporter: Owner and CEO
of Heritage House,

13:22.385 --> 13:24.304
Joseph Sandoval
offered a terse "No --"

13:24.304 --> 13:27.140
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

13:27.140 --> 13:28.850
Antonio, what's up?

13:28.850 --> 13:29.767
Margaret's been talking
to Veronica

13:29.767 --> 13:31.853
about taking over
the company.

13:31.853 --> 13:33.229
They asked me to join forces
with them.

13:33.229 --> 13:34.731
I said no.

13:34.731 --> 13:36.941
I expect them to reach out
to the others.

13:36.941 --> 13:39.110
Take none of the shares
for granted, Apá.

13:39.110 --> 13:41.070
None of them.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.072
I won't forget this,
Antonio.

13:43.072 --> 13:44.073
Don't worry.

13:44.073 --> 13:46.242
I won't let you.

13:46.242 --> 13:51.039
♪♪

13:51.039 --> 13:52.874
Oh, yeah.
How's Denise?

13:52.874 --> 13:54.584
Nearly done
with her PhD.

13:54.584 --> 13:56.669
Oh, my God.
[ Chuckles ]

13:56.669 --> 13:59.047
And Juanito's in Berkeley,
teaching.

13:59.047 --> 14:01.257
Oh, you did such an amazing job
with those kids.

14:01.257 --> 14:03.092
Aww.
I mean, come on.

14:03.092 --> 14:04.761
A single mother, putting herself
through medical school.

14:04.761 --> 14:07.013
How could you do it?

14:07.013 --> 14:08.848
[ Sighs ] How do you think
I could do it?

14:11.559 --> 14:12.769
[ Chuckles ]
[ Speaks Spanish ]

14:12.769 --> 14:14.312
Eso!

14:14.312 --> 14:15.646
Ooh, it's time
for a refill.

14:15.646 --> 14:17.023
[ Chuckles ]

14:17.023 --> 14:18.316
[ Knock on door ]
Please, please, please.

14:18.316 --> 14:19.776
I got it, I got it.

14:25.406 --> 14:27.825
Rosa.
I heard you were in town.

14:28.910 --> 14:30.953
Can I come in?

14:30.953 --> 14:32.497
No law against it,
I suppose.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.584
Kids okay?

14:36.584 --> 14:38.127
They're great.
Thanks.

14:38.127 --> 14:39.921
[ Door closes ]
And your practice?

14:39.921 --> 14:41.798
Why do you ask?
You got a job for me?

14:43.299 --> 14:45.051
We heard about the scabs.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.178
Those scabs are trying to
feed their families,

14:47.178 --> 14:49.097
just like we used to be.
Mm.

14:49.097 --> 14:51.849
Though now that you mention it,
I do remember you saying

14:51.849 --> 14:54.143
I'd never be anything more
than a fruit picker.

14:54.143 --> 14:56.604
[ Chuckles ]
What do you think of
that fruit picker now?

14:56.604 --> 14:57.730
How long do you have?

14:57.730 --> 14:59.482
Joe.

15:06.155 --> 15:08.116
I see your sister
still hates me.

15:08.116 --> 15:09.909
Only mildly.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.369
[ Chuckles ]

15:11.369 --> 15:13.121
What are you
doing here, Joe?

15:14.789 --> 15:17.750
I want you
back in the house.

15:17.750 --> 15:20.044
That's not what you said
yesterday.

15:20.044 --> 15:22.713
I was in shock,

15:22.713 --> 15:24.632
hearing how
my father died.

15:24.632 --> 15:26.676
He begged me
not to tell you, Joe.

15:26.676 --> 15:28.386
Those were
his last words.

15:28.386 --> 15:30.179
Oh, sorry, Lettie.

15:30.179 --> 15:32.390
That must have
been awful.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.142
But I know why
you did what you did.

15:34.142 --> 15:36.352
You were only trying
to protect Margaret.

15:36.352 --> 15:38.020
Still, I should have
told you.

15:38.020 --> 15:40.481
You let me spend
the last 30 years thinking

15:40.481 --> 15:43.568
he was a better man
than he actually was.

15:43.568 --> 15:47.738
It was a --
It was a mercy, Lettie.

15:49.240 --> 15:51.367
I should be
thanking you.

15:51.367 --> 15:54.203
We've always been
a team.

15:54.203 --> 15:58.082
Right? And we built this family
and the company.

15:58.082 --> 16:00.710
I could have never built
Heritage House without you.

16:00.710 --> 16:03.004
[ Sniffles ]
And you know...

16:03.004 --> 16:06.841
I have never given you
the credit you deserve for that.

16:08.259 --> 16:10.553
The company is half yours,
Lettie,

16:10.553 --> 16:12.889
and only 5% of the stock
is in your name?

16:14.974 --> 16:17.852
Well,
I want to fix that.

16:17.852 --> 16:22.231
What do you say
we increase your percentage?

16:22.231 --> 16:23.983
You son of a bitch.

16:23.983 --> 16:25.401
What?

16:25.401 --> 16:27.945
You're scared.

16:27.945 --> 16:30.615
You think I'm gonna sell
my shares to Margaret?

16:30.615 --> 16:32.867
That's ridiculous.
You do.

16:32.867 --> 16:34.410
That's the only reason
you're here.

16:34.410 --> 16:35.870
I want you to leave.

16:35.870 --> 16:37.663
Lettie,
you got it all wrong.
Now!

16:37.663 --> 16:38.831
Now.

16:38.831 --> 16:44.045
♪♪

16:44.045 --> 16:49.592
♪♪

16:49.592 --> 16:52.386
[ Door opens, closes ]

17:07.526 --> 17:10.154
♪ Madre querida ♪

17:10.154 --> 17:12.156
♪ Madre adorada ♪

17:12.156 --> 17:14.033
♪ Dios te bendiga ♪
Man: Hola!

17:14.033 --> 17:15.117
♪ Mi prenda amada ♪

17:32.260 --> 17:33.719
[ Grunts ]

17:33.719 --> 17:38.724
♪♪

17:39.725 --> 17:41.310
[ Man whistles ]

17:41.310 --> 17:44.438
Joe! Joe!
¿Estás bien?

17:45.773 --> 17:47.233
¿Estás bien?

17:47.233 --> 17:49.860
[ Truck doors close,
engine starts ]

17:56.742 --> 17:59.287
[ Speaks Spanish ]

17:59.287 --> 18:02.873
♪♪

18:12.633 --> 18:14.135
Lettie!

18:14.135 --> 18:20.433
♪♪

18:20.433 --> 18:21.517
[ Grunts ]
No.

18:30.860 --> 18:32.612
Joe.

18:33.863 --> 18:35.906
[ Sniffles ]
[ Grunts ]

18:40.286 --> 18:41.871
Oh, Joe.

18:41.871 --> 18:50.004
♪♪

18:50.004 --> 18:52.632
♪ Nada que la pare na, na ♪

18:52.632 --> 18:54.634
♪ No la trates como cualquiera ♪

18:54.634 --> 18:55.885
♪ Le puse el ritmo ♪

18:55.885 --> 18:57.887
What kind of person
spends their entire day

18:57.887 --> 18:59.472
laying by the pool?

18:59.472 --> 19:01.265
For real?

19:01.265 --> 19:03.184
I need help on the vineyard.
Not a lot.

19:03.184 --> 19:04.727
Just you and a dozen of
your high-school buddies.

19:04.727 --> 19:07.688
[ Chuckles ]
You're high.

19:07.688 --> 19:10.024
I can pay them.
They don't need the money.

19:10.024 --> 19:11.817
♪ Y de mi corazón girl tienes
la llave ♪

19:11.817 --> 19:14.362
1520 -- that's what you got
on your SAT score, huh?

19:14.362 --> 19:17.281
That's like
96th percentile.

19:17.281 --> 19:19.241
I'm pretty smart.
Yeah.

19:19.241 --> 19:21.702
Not as smart as the guy you paid
to take the test for you.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.122
How did you know that?

19:25.122 --> 19:27.958
Junior, you and I were in Tahoe
skiing that weekend.

19:27.958 --> 19:29.460
Oh, yeah.

19:29.460 --> 19:32.546
I can't believe Papi would be
too happy to hear about it.

19:32.546 --> 19:35.466
Well, maybe he'll congratulate
me on my initiative.

19:35.466 --> 19:37.426
He's a brown-faced killer,
if you haven't noticed.

19:37.426 --> 19:39.261
Junior, please.

19:39.261 --> 19:42.098
If my harvest is a bust,
I could lose my company.

19:42.098 --> 19:45.309
♪ Ella es asi algo como
Las Vegas ♪

19:45.309 --> 19:46.852
I want equity.

19:46.852 --> 19:48.646
Okay?
And a title.

19:48.646 --> 19:50.189
Oh, I got a title
for you.

19:50.189 --> 19:51.857
♪ Ella se suelta cuando
la noche llega ♪

19:51.857 --> 19:53.984
Okay, fine!
You can have a title.

19:53.984 --> 19:57.363
What, you want
a company car, too?

19:57.363 --> 19:58.989
I got that covered.

19:58.989 --> 20:01.283
[ Screaming ] Stop!

20:01.283 --> 20:03.244
♪ Get your body down
real low ♪

20:03.244 --> 20:05.121
♪ Get your body down
real low ♪

20:05.121 --> 20:06.539
Come on!

20:06.539 --> 20:08.708
Whoo!

20:08.708 --> 20:10.584
♪ Get your body down
real low ♪

20:10.584 --> 20:12.002
♪ Go! Go! ♪

20:12.002 --> 20:13.671
I love a good game
of hardball,

20:13.671 --> 20:15.673
but the former grape picker
locking out his own workers?

20:15.673 --> 20:17.091
The optics are terrible.

20:17.091 --> 20:18.759
No one's going to
lose sleep over this,

20:18.759 --> 20:22.513
and if they do,
they're not our customers.

20:22.513 --> 20:24.849
What is this about, Apá?

20:24.849 --> 20:26.183
Hmm?

20:26.183 --> 20:27.393
Is it Lettie?

20:27.393 --> 20:31.647
♪♪

20:31.647 --> 20:34.108
I know this must have
come as a shock,

20:34.108 --> 20:37.737
but your father's death --
it was an accident.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.989
This is business.
That's all it is.

20:39.989 --> 20:42.283
Then treat it
as the businessman you are.

20:42.283 --> 20:44.744
It starts with a lockout,
and then before you know it,

20:44.744 --> 20:47.079
half the country is boycotting
Heritage House wines.

20:47.079 --> 20:49.206
You don't think I know
the history of boycotts?

20:49.206 --> 20:50.666
I know it better
than anyone.

20:50.666 --> 20:52.168
You're making
a big mistake.

20:52.168 --> 20:54.587
Trust me.

20:54.587 --> 20:57.047
This will be over
before you know it.

20:57.047 --> 21:04.138
♪♪

21:06.640 --> 21:08.100
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:11.729 --> 21:12.688
Joe?

21:14.940 --> 21:16.650
I can't believe
my father did this.

21:16.650 --> 21:19.445
Really, Margaret?
That surprises you?

21:21.197 --> 21:23.783
But he's a good man.
Mm-hmm.

21:23.783 --> 21:25.618
I'm sorry, Margaret,
but he's not.

21:28.120 --> 21:29.330
Hey.

21:33.250 --> 21:34.877
Joe.

21:46.680 --> 21:47.932
Vamos.

21:57.107 --> 21:59.151
Margaret,
this is Hector.

21:59.151 --> 22:01.987
He's worked on the vineyard
for 20 years.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.405
22 in May.

22:05.449 --> 22:07.243
Si, estoy practicando.

22:09.119 --> 22:10.621
You see, Margaret?

22:10.621 --> 22:12.289
That's what this strike
is about.

22:14.792 --> 22:18.128
A better life
for ourselves.

22:18.128 --> 22:21.382
[ Indistinct shouting ]

22:21.382 --> 22:23.008
Hey.
This is getting bad.

22:23.008 --> 22:24.301
You gotta tell your guys
to go home.

22:24.301 --> 22:25.469
Why don't you tell them?

22:25.469 --> 22:27.054
Or better yet,
get your boss down here.

22:27.054 --> 22:28.347
Maybe they'll listen
to him.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.181
Too busy
hiding in his mansion?

22:29.181 --> 22:30.432
Hey! Hey!

22:30.432 --> 22:32.059
You gotta let him through!
Let him pass!

22:35.271 --> 22:36.272
You okay, man?

22:36.272 --> 22:38.649
[ Indistinct shouting ]

22:40.734 --> 22:41.569
Give him room.

22:44.280 --> 22:45.865
Call 911!

22:52.204 --> 22:55.916
Oh, Antonio, sweetie.
How is he?

22:55.916 --> 22:57.376
They don't know.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.169
[ Sighs ]

22:59.169 --> 23:01.672
Gonzo, Clara.

23:01.672 --> 23:02.882
I'm so sorry.

23:02.882 --> 23:04.466
Señora.

23:04.466 --> 23:05.634
It's good of you
to come.

23:05.634 --> 23:09.096
[ Exhales sharply ]
Lettie?

23:09.096 --> 23:11.599
Oh, my God. Rosa.
How are you?

23:11.599 --> 23:13.100
Surprised
to see you here.

23:13.100 --> 23:16.937
Gonzo has served my family
faithfully for over 30 years.

23:16.937 --> 23:18.480
Javi is my godson.

23:18.480 --> 23:21.358
Can we not do this now,
please?

23:21.358 --> 23:24.612
I have an update
on Mr. Soto's condition.

23:24.612 --> 23:26.697
He sustained
a serious head trauma,

23:26.697 --> 23:28.782
which led
to a brain bleed.

23:28.782 --> 23:30.284
Right now, we've got him
on steroids

23:30.284 --> 23:31.452
and anti-seizure medication.

23:31.452 --> 23:32.620
Dexamethasone?

23:32.620 --> 23:33.829
Hopefully he'll respond.

23:33.829 --> 23:35.789
If not,
he'll need surgery,

23:35.789 --> 23:37.625
and the outcomes
get more serious.

23:37.625 --> 23:38.792
Can we see him?

23:38.792 --> 23:39.793
Family can, yes.

23:44.340 --> 23:46.216
You, too.

23:47.927 --> 23:53.140
My son, Gustavo --
he needs medicine.

23:53.140 --> 23:55.559
We no can afford.

23:55.559 --> 23:56.727
Joe: That's why we fight,
Margaret.

23:56.727 --> 23:58.187
You see?

23:58.187 --> 24:02.107
If it takes two weeks

24:02.107 --> 24:05.527
or two years...

24:05.527 --> 24:06.779
we're going to win.

24:06.779 --> 24:08.656
I don't think so, Joe.

24:08.656 --> 24:10.824
We strike
for three weeks now.

24:10.824 --> 24:12.618
People are tired,
hungry.

24:14.620 --> 24:17.957
But mostly,
they are scared.

24:22.002 --> 24:23.754
[ Clears throat ]

24:29.134 --> 24:30.386
Vamos, Hector.
Joe, no.

24:30.386 --> 24:31.720
Thank you, amigo.
Joe.

24:31.720 --> 24:32.888
Margaret,
help me up, please.

24:32.888 --> 24:33.722
¿Te quieres hacer?

24:33.722 --> 24:35.224
Now.
Okay.

24:35.224 --> 24:36.976
[ Grunts ]

24:55.577 --> 24:57.621
Billy.

24:57.621 --> 25:06.338
♪♪

25:06.338 --> 25:15.222
♪♪

25:15.222 --> 25:23.897
♪♪

25:23.897 --> 25:32.573
♪♪

25:32.573 --> 25:41.331
♪♪

25:46.628 --> 25:54.887
♪♪

25:54.887 --> 25:57.222
I'm not in the lease
bit surprised.

25:57.222 --> 25:59.475
I just heard.
How is he?

25:59.475 --> 26:01.268
Oh, now you care.
Rosa.

26:02.644 --> 26:04.480
It's not good.
It's serious, Joe.

26:04.480 --> 26:05.939
He's bleeding
in the brain.

26:05.939 --> 26:07.483
Oh, my God.

26:07.483 --> 26:10.110
This war with your workers
has to stop.

26:10.110 --> 26:12.237
What are you doing?

26:12.237 --> 26:13.781
What is best
for Heritage House.

26:22.498 --> 26:28.796
♪♪

26:28.796 --> 26:31.381
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:31.381 --> 26:33.300
♪♪

26:33.300 --> 26:35.260
Nicely done, bro.

26:35.260 --> 26:36.386
Not my first rodeo.

26:36.386 --> 26:38.222
No, it kind of is.

26:38.222 --> 26:39.848
How'd you get them
to come help out?

26:39.848 --> 26:41.600
I just told them
whoever picks the most grapes

26:41.600 --> 26:42.726
gets a date with you,
so...

26:42.726 --> 26:44.311
Oh, yeah, no.
That's not gonna happen.

26:44.311 --> 26:45.646
I'll let you
think about that one.

26:45.646 --> 26:47.272
No, I already have.
Okay.

26:47.272 --> 26:48.690
Alright, guys.

26:48.690 --> 26:50.192
Everybody has
a pair of these.
Yep.

26:50.192 --> 26:52.111
So we're looking for
clusters of grapes.

26:52.111 --> 26:53.987
You cut as close as you can
to the stem

26:53.987 --> 26:55.280
without
damaging the vine.

26:55.280 --> 26:57.616
You damage the vine,
my sister will kill you.

26:57.616 --> 26:59.284
Those are next year's grapes,
so...

26:59.284 --> 27:01.662
Ready?

27:01.662 --> 27:04.540
These are your workers?
Children of the corn?

27:04.540 --> 27:06.333
The, like, cuter version.

27:06.333 --> 27:08.252
I was up against it.

27:08.252 --> 27:09.795
What about the guys
that Apá fired?

27:09.795 --> 27:11.296
Did you think
about hiring them?

27:11.296 --> 27:13.757
I did, but the man
recently made his will,

27:13.757 --> 27:15.467
and I'm not ready
to be cut out of it.

27:15.467 --> 27:16.969
Bueno.
You got a minute?

27:16.969 --> 27:18.303
Sure.
What's up?

27:18.303 --> 27:21.014
I have an idea.
For the business.

27:21.014 --> 27:23.642
Okay.
You own 5%
of Heritage House.

27:23.642 --> 27:25.102
No, not anymore.

27:25.102 --> 27:27.104
I sold half my shares
to buy the sangria business.

27:27.104 --> 27:29.648
From him.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.525
Hey, Carmen.
Stick 'em up!

27:31.525 --> 27:32.860
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, hey. No.

27:32.860 --> 27:34.570
These are for the grapes,
okay?

27:34.570 --> 27:36.280
Use them on anything else, I'm
gonna use them to cut off --

27:36.280 --> 27:37.865
Okay, Mateo.

27:37.865 --> 27:40.868
Relax.
It's all good.

27:46.456 --> 27:48.500
She was always
your favorite.

27:48.500 --> 27:51.753
[ Sighs ]

27:51.753 --> 27:54.089
I need her 5%.

27:54.089 --> 27:57.384
That's the only reason I offered
to make Veronica CEO.

27:58.719 --> 28:01.054
Once she is on board --
I don't care anymore.

28:01.054 --> 28:03.849
You want to blow up Joe
so bad?

28:03.849 --> 28:05.642
Carlos Rincón.

28:07.352 --> 28:09.187
Did you find out
who he is?

28:09.187 --> 28:11.857
An undocumented worker
who came here 30 years ago

28:11.857 --> 28:15.777
and took the name
Joe Sandoval.

28:15.777 --> 28:18.530
My father's an invention.
A fraud.

28:18.530 --> 28:19.781
That's impossible.

28:19.781 --> 28:22.910
It's the truth.

28:22.910 --> 28:24.703
Because of him,
Javi may not make it.

28:24.703 --> 28:26.997
You wanted a loaded gun?

28:28.290 --> 28:29.666
I just gave you one.

28:31.877 --> 28:34.212
But you're not
gonna use it.

28:34.212 --> 28:36.006
[ Sighs ]

28:36.006 --> 28:37.674
You still love him.

28:40.594 --> 28:42.429
To hell
with both of you.

28:42.429 --> 28:48.226
♪♪

28:48.226 --> 28:50.145
[ Sighs ]

28:50.145 --> 28:56.026
♪♪

28:56.026 --> 28:57.819
[ Exhales sharply ]

29:02.324 --> 29:03.784
Gonna be a long night.

29:05.661 --> 29:07.204
There's a bar
across the street.

29:08.455 --> 29:10.707
Buy you a drink?

29:10.707 --> 29:17.255
♪♪

29:21.885 --> 29:25.097
♪♪

29:25.097 --> 29:26.682
Veronica: Joe and Margaret
have already shown us

29:26.682 --> 29:28.183
where they'll take
this company.

29:28.183 --> 29:30.018
I think
there's a better way.

29:30.018 --> 29:34.231
You want us, the kids,
to take over Heritage House?

29:34.231 --> 29:36.692
I got my own label now.
Carmen's got the sangria.

29:36.692 --> 29:37.985
I mean, Joe's been
a thorn in my side,

29:37.985 --> 29:39.695
but there's no denying
what he's built.

29:39.695 --> 29:42.239
Plus, I already borrowed against
my shares to run this place.

29:42.239 --> 29:43.865
So it must be killing you to see
the what the stocks are doing

29:43.865 --> 29:46.076
with this labor fight.
What's in it for us?

29:46.076 --> 29:48.829
I mean, if we throw in with you,
what do we get?

29:48.829 --> 29:50.497
Well, right now,
you have a sangria business

29:50.497 --> 29:53.959
that's killing it in California
but nowhere else.

29:53.959 --> 29:55.961
You know the life-span
of speciality drinks

29:55.961 --> 29:57.587
if you don't break into
international markets,

29:57.587 --> 29:59.214
or national ones at least,

29:59.214 --> 30:01.717
and neither of those options are
on the table for you right now.

30:01.717 --> 30:04.511
Let's face it -- at the moment,
you have a roadside stand.

30:04.511 --> 30:06.304
A little harsh, V.

30:06.304 --> 30:08.265
You have high-school students
picking your grapes, Carmen.

30:08.265 --> 30:10.350
I don't.
No.

30:10.350 --> 30:12.144
What you have here
is special.

30:12.144 --> 30:14.062
But it's gonna take a couple
of years, at least.

30:14.062 --> 30:16.857
Mateo,
you're a winemaker.

30:16.857 --> 30:19.317
Joe's the only one
who didn't see that.

30:19.317 --> 30:20.944
So while you get this place
up and running,

30:20.944 --> 30:22.654
how would you like to create
your own label

30:22.654 --> 30:24.614
under the Heritage House
banner?

30:24.614 --> 30:27.325
You can call it
Mateo's Reserve.

30:27.325 --> 30:29.411
You'll have better grapes,
much better marketing,

30:29.411 --> 30:31.705
and within a year,

30:31.705 --> 30:33.707
you'll be on the cover
of Wine Life Magazine.

30:33.707 --> 30:35.584
You think I care about
being on the cover of
Wine Life Magazine?

30:35.584 --> 30:37.252
Yes.
Yes.

30:37.252 --> 30:39.212
Fair enough.

30:39.212 --> 30:43.425
Okay, even if we did do this,
there's one little problem.

30:43.425 --> 30:44.843
Papi never loses.

30:44.843 --> 30:47.637
Papi's also never been up
against all his kids at once.

30:49.056 --> 30:50.640
I'm putting together
a siblings-only meeting

30:50.640 --> 30:52.684
tomorrow at noon.

30:52.684 --> 30:54.144
If you're in...

30:54.144 --> 30:56.188
I need you there.

30:56.188 --> 31:00.692
♪♪

31:00.692 --> 31:03.487
[ Vehicle door opens, closes ]

31:03.487 --> 31:04.529
[ Engine starts ]

31:08.325 --> 31:09.576
Where is everybody?

31:09.576 --> 31:12.079
They left.
All of them?

31:12.079 --> 31:14.498
You know, manual labor's
not really their thing.

31:14.498 --> 31:16.541
It's not your thing,
and you're still here.

31:16.541 --> 31:18.085
You're my sister.
It's a little bit different.

31:21.379 --> 31:23.632
You can go if you want.

31:23.632 --> 31:25.842
[ Scoffs ]
No, I'm not going home.

31:25.842 --> 31:27.677
There's no way we're gonna
harvest all of this.

31:27.677 --> 31:31.515
There's at least...
3,000 vines.

31:31.515 --> 31:33.558
Then I'll take 2,000
and you take 1,000.

31:35.477 --> 31:37.062
Come on.

31:37.062 --> 31:38.772
Okay.

31:38.772 --> 31:47.447
♪♪

31:47.447 --> 31:49.825
Funny how a thing
like a corporate takeover

31:49.825 --> 31:53.578
seems so life-and-death until
real life and death intrudes.

31:53.578 --> 31:55.372
Does that mean you're giving up
on the takeover?

31:57.332 --> 32:01.128
You know, it's your fault
we're in this position.

32:01.128 --> 32:02.963
Oh, really?

32:02.963 --> 32:04.256
How's that?

32:04.256 --> 32:06.508
A rich girl --
someone like you

32:06.508 --> 32:08.552
could fall in love
with someone like me.

32:08.552 --> 32:11.138
It made me feel like
I could conquer the word.

32:11.138 --> 32:14.099
When you're 20,
that's everything.

32:14.099 --> 32:16.017
What if I hadn't
fallen in love with you?

32:16.017 --> 32:18.353
I wouldn't own the company
you're trying to take from me.

32:18.353 --> 32:21.106
So, like I said,
your fault.

32:23.150 --> 32:24.776
And yet,
I don't feel bad.

32:24.776 --> 32:26.820
You shouldn't.
You inspired me.

32:26.820 --> 32:28.155
Hmm.

32:28.155 --> 32:29.990
At least I've got that
on Lettie.

32:29.990 --> 32:38.123
♪♪

32:38.123 --> 32:39.583
What?
Nothing.

32:39.583 --> 32:41.585
Come on.
Out with it.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.463
Okay.

32:47.257 --> 32:49.551
Joe, have you ever thought
of us teaming up?

32:49.551 --> 32:51.720
[ Chuckles ]
That's the alcohol talking.

32:51.720 --> 32:53.513
No, think about it.

32:53.513 --> 32:55.599
With my hotels
and your vineyards,

32:55.599 --> 32:57.100
we make
a pretty strong combo,

32:57.100 --> 32:59.895
and we've always seen the world
the same way.

32:59.895 --> 33:04.065
Together,
we'd be unstoppable.

33:04.065 --> 33:05.734
Okay,
time to cut you off.

33:05.734 --> 33:07.569
No, I'm serious.

33:07.569 --> 33:10.030
Take this thing with
the replacement workers.

33:10.030 --> 33:11.406
How many people think
you're doing the right thing?

33:11.406 --> 33:12.782
You'd be the first.
Yeah.

33:12.782 --> 33:15.952
Because everybody blames
the owners.

33:15.952 --> 33:18.288
They don't understand
that giving people a job --

33:18.288 --> 33:19.664
that's not nothing.

33:19.664 --> 33:21.416
[ Scoffs ]
Instead of being appreciated,

33:21.416 --> 33:23.501
we're reviled.
Mm.

33:23.501 --> 33:25.003
No, what you're doing --
it's exactly what

33:25.003 --> 33:26.379
my father
would have done.

33:28.465 --> 33:31.384
Your father and I
are nothing alike.

33:31.384 --> 33:32.969
You know that's not
what I meant.

33:32.969 --> 33:35.555
I started in the fields.
He had everything handed to him.

33:35.555 --> 33:37.182
He was a racist.

33:37.182 --> 33:39.351
I try my damndest
not to judge a man

33:39.351 --> 33:40.644
based on the color
of his skin.

33:40.644 --> 33:43.396
I hired
replacement workers.

33:43.396 --> 33:46.650
He hired goons to beat the hell
out of anyone who opposed him.

33:52.364 --> 33:53.448
We're nothing alike.

33:55.951 --> 33:57.869
And you never
inspired me.

33:57.869 --> 33:59.955
[ Exhales sharply ]

33:59.955 --> 34:03.333
It's always been Lettie,
and it always will be.

34:03.333 --> 34:09.673
♪♪

34:09.673 --> 34:13.885
I own 29% of Heritage House,
with another 10 pledged.

34:13.885 --> 34:16.972
That means I only need 12%
to come my way

34:16.972 --> 34:19.391
during
the shareholders meeting.

34:19.391 --> 34:25.105
And you best believe
I will not pull punches.

34:25.105 --> 34:28.692
I will blow you sky high.

34:28.692 --> 34:30.485
Like you ever could.

34:30.485 --> 34:32.112
You don't understand.

34:33.154 --> 34:35.365
I can destroy you.

34:35.365 --> 34:38.243
Bring it on.

34:38.243 --> 34:44.082
♪♪

34:44.082 --> 34:49.838
♪♪

34:52.340 --> 34:54.884
Young Margaret:
Joe.

34:54.884 --> 34:56.970
He wants to make a deal.

34:56.970 --> 34:58.930
He'll give the workers
another 10-minute break a day,

34:58.930 --> 35:01.016
he'll guarantee all the trailers
will have water and electricity,

35:01.016 --> 35:03.893
and he's willing to go up
an extra 15 cents an hour.

35:03.893 --> 35:07.856
♪ Y aunque muy lejos estés ♪

35:07.856 --> 35:09.274
It's a start.

35:09.274 --> 35:11.109
A start?

35:11.109 --> 35:12.819
This is the best deal
you're going to get.

35:12.819 --> 35:14.404
Hey, no,
Margaret's right.

35:15.196 --> 35:16.865
I don't think so.

35:16.865 --> 35:18.992
♪ Si tu te ríes ♪

35:23.830 --> 35:25.206
Why are you
so stubborn?

35:25.206 --> 35:27.417
Because I know
what is right.

35:27.417 --> 35:28.793
And soon,
so will your father.

35:28.793 --> 35:32.255
♪♪

35:32.255 --> 35:35.091
He'll listen to you.

35:35.091 --> 35:36.468
Please, say something.

35:36.468 --> 35:38.386
♪ Camino ♪

35:38.386 --> 35:41.598
♪ El que nos hizo encontrar ♪

35:41.598 --> 35:43.266
No deal.

35:43.266 --> 35:44.851
♪ Dos almas ♪

35:44.851 --> 35:46.853
Leticia.
No, Billy.

35:46.853 --> 35:48.480
Joe, can you please
just listen?

35:48.480 --> 35:53.068
Margaret...you live
in a big house

35:53.068 --> 35:55.779
with a nice view.

35:55.779 --> 35:58.239
You have no right to tell us
what is best.

35:58.239 --> 36:03.703
♪ El faro que alumbrará ♪

36:12.671 --> 36:14.589
Hey, Margaret!

36:14.589 --> 36:21.638
♪♪

36:21.638 --> 36:24.599
♪ Tu corazon y el mío ♪

36:33.316 --> 36:34.984
Si.

36:34.984 --> 36:39.114
♪ Lo que hicimos ya nacer
y florecer ♪

36:39.114 --> 36:40.198
Juana.

36:40.198 --> 36:42.492
♪ Alli ♪

36:42.492 --> 36:47.122
♪ Donde tu vayas, yo iré ♪

36:47.122 --> 36:51.710
♪ Y aunque muy lejos estés ♪

36:51.710 --> 36:55.714
♪ Siempre a tu lado estaré ♪

36:55.714 --> 37:00.760
♪ Siempre a tu lado estaré ♪

37:00.760 --> 37:05.014
♪ Siempre a tu lado estaré ♪

37:05.014 --> 37:08.768
♪ Siempre a tu lado ♪

37:08.768 --> 37:15.275
♪ Siempre a tu lado estaré ♪

37:20.113 --> 37:25.577
♪♪

37:25.577 --> 37:27.370
[ Insects chirping ]

37:30.665 --> 37:32.208
It's for a good cause.
Pbht!

37:32.208 --> 37:33.585
Sangria?

37:33.585 --> 37:35.795
No. You.

37:35.795 --> 37:37.380
No one thought
you could do it.

37:37.380 --> 37:40.508
You owe me, though.

37:40.508 --> 37:41.885
It's supposed to be 90
today.

37:41.885 --> 37:43.470
There's no way we pick
all these grapes

37:43.470 --> 37:45.472
by the hot part of the day,
and we'll lose half my crop.

37:45.472 --> 37:46.890
If you stand there talking,
you will.

37:46.890 --> 37:48.850
♪♪

37:48.850 --> 37:50.435
We finished one of our blocks
ahead of schedule.

37:50.435 --> 37:52.061
Carmen, Junior,
you both know Nando.

37:52.061 --> 37:54.022
This is Joaquin and Lupita.

37:55.356 --> 37:58.902
See? I told you I can get down
in the dirt if I have to.

37:58.902 --> 38:00.695
[ Chuckles ]
Whatever you say, princess.

38:00.695 --> 38:02.489
Gracias.

38:02.489 --> 38:03.490
De nada.

38:03.490 --> 38:04.949
Gracias.
De nada.

38:04.949 --> 38:10.330
♪♪

38:10.330 --> 38:11.915
5% increase.

38:11.915 --> 38:13.750
It's not the 6%
you wanted,

38:13.750 --> 38:16.336
but it's more than
the cost of living.

38:16.336 --> 38:19.130
That's doable.

38:19.130 --> 38:20.799
As for health care,

38:20.799 --> 38:22.884
I'll cover the 70%
you asked for.

38:22.884 --> 38:26.304
In addition, we will provide
free ESL instruction

38:26.304 --> 38:28.932
to any worker
who wants it.

38:31.392 --> 38:32.977
I'll take "yes"
for an answer.

38:32.977 --> 38:35.063
Uh...

38:35.063 --> 38:37.440
yes.

38:37.440 --> 38:40.318
Now, about that rule
that says that organizers

38:40.318 --> 38:42.445
can't meet with union workers
on your property --

38:42.445 --> 38:43.988
Eh, I like that rule.

38:43.988 --> 38:45.782
It hurts workers.
It hurts you.

38:45.782 --> 38:47.700
I can't give you everything,
Tomás.

38:47.700 --> 38:49.786
I do have
some self-respect.

38:53.665 --> 38:55.458
[ Sighs ]

38:59.045 --> 39:01.089
[ Monitor beeping ]

39:04.884 --> 39:06.094
[ Exhales slowly ]

39:06.094 --> 39:12.517
♪♪

39:12.517 --> 39:15.395
Javi?

39:15.395 --> 39:18.106
There you are.

39:18.106 --> 39:24.153
♪♪

39:25.655 --> 39:28.199
[ Bottle top pops ]

39:28.199 --> 39:30.660
Mm.
How'd it go?

39:30.660 --> 39:32.745
[ Chuckles ]
Kicked my ass.

39:32.745 --> 39:35.123
But I loved
every minute of it.

39:35.123 --> 39:37.625
Ugh.

39:37.625 --> 39:39.085
You're your father's son.

39:39.085 --> 39:40.628
[ Chuckles ]

39:40.628 --> 39:41.921
Where do you think
he went?

39:41.921 --> 39:45.633
I was talking about Joe,
the man who raised you.

39:45.633 --> 39:47.552
I have no idea
where he went.

39:49.596 --> 39:51.347
You sure you can't stay
one more day?

39:51.347 --> 39:53.141
I have to get back
to Fresno.

39:53.141 --> 39:55.310
If I'm not at the hospital
when rounds start

39:55.310 --> 39:56.477
[exhales sharply]

39:56.477 --> 39:57.937
God knows what the residents
will get up to.

39:57.937 --> 40:00.690
[ Both chuckle ]

40:00.690 --> 40:02.066
[ Sighs ]

40:02.066 --> 40:03.776
I'm sorry I didn't get
to meet Daniela.

40:03.776 --> 40:06.070
Sorry.
She sounds amazing.

40:06.070 --> 40:08.156
Yeah. She comes back
from El Salvador next week.

40:08.156 --> 40:09.282
You really gotta meet her.

40:09.282 --> 40:10.533
And not let
another six years go by

40:10.533 --> 40:12.744
before your next visit.
Oh, I won't.

40:12.744 --> 40:14.078
Okay.

40:17.040 --> 40:18.374
Is she where
I think she is?

40:18.374 --> 40:23.880
♪♪

40:23.880 --> 40:29.302
♪♪

40:35.141 --> 40:42.774
♪♪

40:42.774 --> 40:45.026
Hola, Marta.
Buenos dias.

40:45.026 --> 40:46.361
The lockout's over.
Que bien.

40:46.361 --> 40:47.654
Congratulations.

40:47.654 --> 40:49.822
Call the kids.
Let's have a big lunch.

40:49.822 --> 40:51.407
We'll open the Reserva.

40:51.407 --> 40:52.617
Absolutamente.

40:54.744 --> 40:56.579
[ Door opens ]

40:56.579 --> 41:04.963
♪♪

41:04.963 --> 41:13.054
♪♪

41:13.054 --> 41:21.437
♪♪

41:21.437 --> 41:22.981
Hello, Joe.

41:25.149 --> 41:26.859
[ Chuckles ]

41:29.737 --> 41:32.073
It's over, Lettie.
I made a deal with the workers.

41:32.073 --> 41:34.325
Yeah, I heard.
I'm glad.

41:34.325 --> 41:36.035
You heard about
the ESL classes?

41:36.035 --> 41:38.162
I knew that would
make you happy.

41:38.162 --> 41:40.206
I'm giving you
my shares, Joe.

41:40.206 --> 41:41.457
Lettie,
I didn't mean --

41:41.457 --> 41:42.792
No, it's okay.
I don't need them.

41:45.878 --> 41:47.338
I'm leaving you, Joe.

41:56.889 --> 42:00.643
[ Voice breaking ] Lettie.
I love you.

42:00.643 --> 42:01.769
You love me.

42:06.607 --> 42:07.859
[ Scoffs ]

42:10.486 --> 42:13.239
You're talking nonsense.

42:13.239 --> 42:14.782
Goodbye, Joe.

42:14.782 --> 42:16.701
Lettie.
Come back here, Lettie!

42:17.869 --> 42:19.162
Fine.
Go if you want,

42:19.162 --> 42:21.289
but don't bother
coming back!

42:21.289 --> 42:23.499
You hear me?!

42:23.499 --> 42:25.043
Juana?!

42:27.962 --> 42:30.256
[ Door closes ]
I don't want you!

42:31.424 --> 42:37.138
♪ All of our time
chasing a dream ♪

42:38.389 --> 42:41.768
♪ Mm, mm, mm ♪

42:41.768 --> 42:46.147
♪ A dream that meant nothing
to me ♪

42:46.147 --> 42:48.524
Big turnout.

42:48.524 --> 42:49.776
You're late.

42:51.277 --> 42:52.862
Mexican time.

42:52.862 --> 42:54.363
[ Chuckles ]

42:54.363 --> 42:56.574
♪ Where they all lay ♪

42:56.574 --> 42:58.534
♪ All of the greats ♪

42:58.534 --> 43:00.369
No snacks?

43:00.369 --> 43:02.538
Well, in V's defense, she threw
this together last minute.

43:05.374 --> 43:08.711
♪ Here in America ♪

43:08.711 --> 43:09.837
Antonio: Buenas.

43:12.173 --> 43:15.343
♪ And I hope
that you're finding ♪

43:15.343 --> 43:17.595
♪ All that you are ♪

43:17.595 --> 43:21.265
♪ I hope that it sets you up ♪

43:21.265 --> 43:23.142
First off,
thank you for coming.

43:25.353 --> 43:26.687
Second...

43:26.687 --> 43:29.357
♪ In the heart of America ♪

43:29.357 --> 43:32.819
...let's talk about how
to take back Heritage House.

43:32.819 --> 43:39.742
♪ I'll just be left
here in America ♪

43:41.077 --> 43:44.080
♪ But she never had
a home for me ♪

43:50.461 --> 44:00.054
♪♪

44:00.054 --> 44:09.480
♪♪

44:09.480 --> 44:18.823
♪♪
